Is anyone getting this thing to work reliably? I'm one of three people
I know using it, and it's failing more than it's working for us.

The disk will just drop off the network. I suppose it might be related
to me putting the laptop to sleep without dismounting, but really it
should be able to cope with the loss of a network connection. The disk
will then either not appear for mounting again, or sometimes will
appear but reject every password I offer it.

Should it reject the password, then in the logs it will say &quot;this disk
needs minor repairs&quot;. Of course it will give no indication of this from
the client side, you're left just guessing why it's rejecting a
perfectly good password.

It's a major pain - I'm hoping at some point in the future to start
using Airport Disk for backups via Time Machine, but at the moment I'm
barely using it for anything at all as it simply doesn't work reliably
enough.

